  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate, nominal-only validation)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML surrogate model trained to predict pump-induced hemolysis for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Validation evidence covers only nominal operating conditions drawn from the same distribution as training data. No robustness characterization, covariate-shift study, noise-injection experiment, or adversarial perturbation evaluation has been performed or reported.",
