      "name": "Nominal test-set accuracy — ML surrogate hemolysis prediction",
      "description": "The ML surrogate was evaluated on a held-out test set sampled from the same distribution as the training corpus (5 nominal flow-speed operating points, 120 CFD-derived samples). Mean absolute error in relative hemolysis index (RH) was 0.031 across all test points. Coefficient of determination R² = 0.964. All predictions satisfied the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Evaluation was performed exclusively on in-distribution nominal operating conditions.",
      "metric": "Mean absolute error (MAE) = 0.031; R² = 0.964",
      "passFailStatus": "Pass"
